    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Follow up open deals with Google Drive and Telegram in real time\n\n**Pattern:** Reminders & Follow-ups · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nFollow up open deals with Google Drive and Telegram in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual follow-ups is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Normalize Contact Payload → Segment Audience → Step 1 — Welcome (Telegram) → Wait Before Step 2 → Converted Already? → Step 2 — Value Nudge (Telegram) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to reminders & follow-ups without manual effort\n- Anyone automating follow-ups in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Improves response time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "53f04bcc-5c46-3910-0697-fb174d370c6c",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "c4521ee7-fd7a-1521-a2e4-d007a46c5a45",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "d873953c-5071-07d4-6b3a-35916dbdf3cc",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your follow-ups process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
